    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "\"In this study, we systematically evaluate the cognitive limits of large language models (LLMs) on complex logical reasoning, employing a comprehensive benchmark that spans 10 distinct model architectures. By analyzing 5,000 instances across four reasoning stages, we demonstrate that step‑3 processing is a critical bottleneck, with a 23% drop in accuracy that is statistically significant (p < 0.01). These findings not only underscore the current boundaries of AI reasoning but also point to actionable pathways for future model improvements. We anticipate that this work will resonate with readers in Nature and inspire broader investigations into the scalability of AI cognition.\"",
      "source": "target",
